==English==

{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[bece|bēċe]]'', from Germanic ''*bōkjōn'', a derivative of ''*bōkō'', from Indo-European ''*bhagos''.  Cognate with Dutch ''[[beuk]]'', German ''[[Buche]]'', Swedish ''[[bok]]''; and with Greek [[φηγός]] ‘oak’, Latin ''[[fagus]]'' ‘beech’, Russian [[бузина]] ‘elder (tree)’.  Compare ''[[buckwheat]]'', ''[[book]]''.

